subparagraph.text:
the particular
				unit of the governmental entity responsible for safe and appropriate operation
				of the public unmanned aircraft system;

the rank and title
				of the individual who may authorize the operation of the public unmanned
				aircraft system;

authorizing the operation of a public
				unmanned aircraft system only in a stipulated public area for a period of not
				more than 48 hours;

which may be renewed at the court’s
				discretion for a total period of operation of not longer than 30 days;
				and

clause.text:
requires such operation, collection, or
				disclosure before a warrant or order authorizing such operation, collection, or
				disclosure may, with due diligence, be obtained;

paragraph.text:
the fact that the
				order or extension was granted as applied for, was modified, or was
				denied;

the period of
				collections authorized by the order, and the number and duration of any
				extensions of the order;

subparagraph.text:
the approximate
				nature, amount, and cost of the manpower and other resources used in the
				collection;

paragraph.text:
the number of arrests resulting from
				covered information collected from such order or extension, and the offenses
				for which arrests were made;
